---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout active="home">
<header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="brandline display">
      <svg width="22" height="24" viewBox="0 0 22 24" aria-hidden="true">
        <polygon points="11,1 20.5,6.5 20.5,17.5 11,23 1.5,17.5 1.5,6.5"
                 fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
      </svg>
      Beadhive · Field Guide
    </div>
    <h1 class="display">Agentic Git Flow, driven by beads</h1>
    <p class="lede">How the Beadhive factory turns raw ideas into an always-green integration
    branch — with agents doing the work, humans holding the gates, and a dependency-linked
    issue tracker (<em>beads</em>) as the shared memory that makes both possible.</p>

    <div class="namestack display">
      <div class="namecard"><b>AGF — Agentic Git Flow</b>
        <span>The abstract, tracker-independent process: operational planes, seats,
        worktree-per-bead, review gates, serialized merges.</span></div>
      <div class="namecard"><b>Beadflow</b>
        <span>AGF implemented on beads — the concrete process this repo runs. Same behavior,
        bead-backed.</span></div>
      <div class="namecard"><b>Beadhive · <code>bh</code></b>
        <span>The umbrella brand and its CLI: the integration-plane driver that encodes the
        conventions, registry, validation, and routing.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="teasers">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow display">The field guide · four chapters</div>
    <div class="cardgrid">
      <a class="card teaser" href="/beads/">
        <h4><span class="hexdot">⬢</span>The substrate</h4>
        <p><b>Beads</b> (<code>bd</code>) is a lightweight, git-embedded issue tracker with
        first-class dependency support — the durable shared memory that makes agents effective,
        and the opinions on why it beats markdown TODOs or a hosted tracker.</p>
        <span class="cardcta display">Read Beads →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card teaser" href="/process/">
        <h4><span class="hexdot">⬢</span>How work flows</h4>
        <p>Every repo is a <b>hive</b>, and <code>bh</code> drives each bead through worktree →
        implement → review → merge on an always-green line — the full state machine with its
        plan, kickoff, and review gates.</p>
        <span class="cardcta display">Read Process →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card teaser" href="/roles/">
        <h4><span class="hexdot">⬢</span>Who does what</h4>
        <p>One process, two kinds of worker: humans hold the gates, agents do the work. Four
        planes and their seats, separated by blast radius.</p>
        <span class="cardcta display">Read Roles →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card teaser" href="/fleet/">
        <h4><span class="hexdot">⬢</span>Scale</h4>
        <p>A fleet of hives, one Head Office: <code>bh sync</code> aggregates every registered
        hive so you can ask what's actionable anywhere, plus where the source-of-truth docs
        live.</p>
        <span class="cardcta display">Read Fleet →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
